WEBVTT

00:02.567 --> 00:04.134
So, what's the story, kids?
You buying the place,

00:04.178 --> 00:06.528
or am I letting Alviti
turn it into a parking lot?

00:06.571 --> 00:08.051
We're having
a bit of trouble

00:08.095 --> 00:09.748
coming up
with the whole down payment.

00:09.792 --> 00:10.836
How short are you?

00:10.880 --> 00:13.143
The whole down payment.

00:13.187 --> 00:14.753
The guy's
putting pressure on me.

00:14.797 --> 00:17.234
I gotta give him a decision
by the end of the week.

00:17.278 --> 00:20.063
Oh, who are we kidding?
We can't buy this place.

00:20.107 --> 00:22.283
Or canyou?

00:22.326 --> 00:24.546
No, we can't.

00:24.589 --> 00:27.375
Chale, in this country,
when someone dramatically says,

00:27.418 --> 00:29.464
"Or can you?"
that's a good thing.

00:29.507 --> 00:31.944
Kids, I have
completely drained my 401[k].

00:31.988 --> 00:33.642
I'm going to invest
in your dream.

00:33.685 --> 00:34.904
Wait. What?
What?!

00:34.947 --> 00:36.166
Uncle Kyle!
Uh!

00:36.210 --> 00:37.863
-That's unbe--
-There is a string attached.

00:37.907 --> 00:40.388
When the new place opens,
I want a beer named after me.

00:40.431 --> 00:42.651
Oh, good call.
Yeah.

00:42.694 --> 00:44.740
I want the Kyle Gable name
to live on.

00:44.783 --> 00:46.220
It'll be my legacy,
you know.

00:46.263 --> 00:48.091
Kind of like Sam Adams.

00:48.135 --> 00:49.919
You do realize
that Sam Adams was famous

00:49.962 --> 00:51.703
before he had a beer
named after him, right?

00:51.747 --> 00:54.141
Yeah, but it doesn't matter.
I just know him for the beer.

00:54.184 --> 00:55.620
Okay, well...
Yeah.

00:55.664 --> 00:56.752
Of course.
Of course we can.
Yeah! Yeah!

00:56.795 --> 00:58.580
You got a check from me!
Oh, my gosh!

00:58.623 --> 01:00.016
This is so amazing.
We were just --

01:00.060 --> 01:02.584
The numbers, and we just...
Hmm.

01:02.627 --> 01:05.239
Um, this is for $6,000.

01:05.282 --> 01:08.285
You told us that you had
over $100,000 in your 401[k].

01:08.329 --> 01:09.765
Yeah.
Mistakes were made.

01:09.808 --> 01:11.114
Um...

01:11.158 --> 01:13.812
Most recently, I got
into the Bitcoin market.

01:13.856 --> 01:15.075
Bought a bunch.

01:15.118 --> 01:17.990
Turns out they were
just old subway tokens.

01:18.034 --> 01:20.123
-What's goin' on, boys?
-Hey, hey, hey!

01:20.167 --> 01:23.126
Eh, we're just talkin' about
Enzo's being turned to dust.

01:23.170 --> 01:24.388
Kevin: Oh, yeah.

01:24.432 --> 01:25.650
Lotta memories here.

01:25.694 --> 01:28.175
I met Cindy
at the end of the bar.

01:28.218 --> 01:29.785
I was wiping crumbs
off my shirt.

01:29.828 --> 01:31.395
She thought I was trying
to dance with her.

01:31.439 --> 01:36.008
To this day, she still thinks
this is an actual dance move.

01:36.052 --> 01:38.185
Yeah, and it was right over
there where I became a champion.

01:38.228 --> 01:40.274
[ Laughs ]
Still get chills.

01:40.317 --> 01:41.666
Oh, yeah.
Champion?

01:41.710 --> 01:44.234
Yeah. Back in the day,
Enzo's had a Whack-a-Mole,

01:44.278 --> 01:47.759
and I was the champion
from 1989 to '92.

01:47.803 --> 01:49.152
Really?

01:49.196 --> 01:51.459
Yes, really.

01:51.502 --> 01:53.809
You got this.
Yeah, I do.

01:54.505 --> 01:56.812
[ Coin clinks ]
Get it.

01:56.855 --> 01:58.988
Get it. Get it.
Get it. Get it. Get it.
[ Bell dinging ]

01:59.031 --> 02:00.163
Get some. Get some.
Get it. Get it.

02:00.207 --> 02:01.382
Oh, hey, get it.
Get it. Get it.

02:01.425 --> 02:02.513
Get some more.
Get it.

02:02.557 --> 02:03.906
Get some more.
Get more. Get it. Get it.

02:03.949 --> 02:05.690
Get it. Get some.
Get some more.

02:05.734 --> 02:06.996
[ Bell dings ]
Oh, God.

02:07.039 --> 02:08.432
Get some more.
Get it. Get some more.

02:08.476 --> 02:09.477
Get some more. Get it.
Get some more. There you go.

02:09.520 --> 02:10.652
[ Buzzer ]
Yeah!

02:10.695 --> 02:11.783
Ha!

02:11.827 --> 02:12.915
[ Grunts ]

02:12.958 --> 02:14.917
Whoo!
Waaa!

02:17.702 --> 02:19.748
Man, those were
some good times.

02:19.791 --> 02:22.533
I remember
the first time I came here.

02:22.577 --> 02:24.274
Crazy story.

02:24.318 --> 02:27.495
Uh, Diet Coke, please.
You got it.

02:31.368 --> 02:33.849
That's it? That --
That's the whole story?

02:33.892 --> 02:35.329
I've only been here
a few times.

02:35.372 --> 02:36.721
That was the best
out of three.

02:36.765 --> 02:38.070
[ Scoffs ]

02:38.114 --> 02:39.550
You know, another great
memory here was that time

02:39.594 --> 02:42.553
I-I surprised you guys
with that check for $80,000.

02:42.597 --> 02:43.554
Remember that one?
-No.

02:43.598 --> 02:44.555
No,
I don't remember that.

02:44.599 --> 02:45.556
That's right.

02:45.600 --> 02:47.602
'Cause it's happening now!

02:47.645 --> 02:48.864
Ba-boom!

02:48.907 --> 02:50.082
What?!
What?!

02:50.126 --> 02:51.519
Yes!
Dad, what --
How did you do this?

02:51.562 --> 02:53.521
No.
I took out a second mortgage
on the house.

02:53.564 --> 02:55.131
What?! $80,000?

02:55.175 --> 02:57.351
This -- That's more than enough
for the down payment!

02:57.394 --> 02:59.875
That's right. We're gonna buy
Enzo's, is what we're doing.

02:59.918 --> 03:02.007
[ Laughs ] Wait.
Now, Dad, are you sure?

03:02.051 --> 03:03.183
This is a lot of money.

03:03.226 --> 03:04.445
I've never been more sure

03:04.488 --> 03:05.881
about anything in my life,
all right?

03:05.924 --> 03:07.230
Dad, thank you!
I love you!

03:07.274 --> 03:08.579
This is --

03:08.623 --> 03:10.233
You know, it seems like
he's got things covered,

03:10.277 --> 03:12.061
so it's probably best
if -- if I get my check back,

03:12.104 --> 03:14.150
'cause that thing's gonna
bounce like a basketball.

03:15.804 --> 03:20.722
♪ I am not your ordinary guy

03:20.765 --> 03:22.158
[ Knock on door ]
We do that twice a week.

03:22.202 --> 03:23.159
Twice.
That would be...

03:23.203 --> 03:24.160
-Hey!
-Hey!

03:24.204 --> 03:25.857
Come on!
We have to go to work!

03:25.901 --> 03:27.642
Yeah. I just got to grab
my wallet upstairs, all right?

03:27.685 --> 03:29.818
Right now, I'm just kickin'
around ideas for the new Enzo's.

03:29.861 --> 03:31.428
And now, are we clear
on what I want?

03:31.472 --> 03:33.735
I guess so, but you do
understand Whack-a-Mole

03:33.778 --> 03:35.519
is a kids' game, right?
No, no, no.

03:35.563 --> 03:36.955
It's all about
hand-eye coordination

03:36.999 --> 03:38.609
and -- and --
and mental recognition.

03:38.653 --> 03:40.394
He's right.
NASA use it

03:40.437 --> 03:43.005
for their astronauts to work
on their cognitive abilities

03:43.048 --> 03:44.572
before they embark
on a mission.

03:44.615 --> 03:46.051
Oh.
Seriously?

03:46.095 --> 03:48.576
No. It's a children's game
wherein they're taught

03:48.619 --> 03:51.535
to bash adorable things
with a mallet.

03:51.579 --> 03:53.885
Okay, look.
I knew this was gonna happen.

03:53.929 --> 03:55.060
I knew
once you bought the bar,

03:55.104 --> 03:57.411
you would lose focus
on your real job.

03:57.454 --> 03:58.934
I can multitask, okay?

03:58.977 --> 04:00.762
Dad, we really appreciate
your help,

04:00.805 --> 04:03.286
but Chale and I kinda know
what we wanna do with it.

04:03.330 --> 04:05.810
Yes, we were thinking
of modernizing the place,

04:05.854 --> 04:07.595
maybe
some signature coffee.

04:07.638 --> 04:08.639
[ Imitating buzzer ]

04:10.685 --> 04:12.904
Ugh!
You gotta listen.

04:12.948 --> 04:14.297
Enzo's has a certain charm.

04:14.341 --> 04:15.559
We wanna keep that charm.

04:15.603 --> 04:17.213
And you wanna do that
with Whack-a-Mole?

04:17.257 --> 04:18.736
For starters,
yeah, I do, okay?

04:18.780 --> 04:20.521
And I got a whole bunch of ideas
running around in my head.

04:20.564 --> 04:23.132
So, here --
Okay, well,
those are so amazing.

04:23.175 --> 04:24.742
Why don't
you go grab your stuff,

04:24.786 --> 04:26.222
and we will go over
the details, okay?

04:26.266 --> 04:27.658
F-- That's all right.
Perfect.
Yes.

04:27.702 --> 04:29.051
I'm very happy about it.
This is gonna be good, guys?

04:29.094 --> 04:30.270
-Very happy. Very happy.
-Okay, yes!

04:30.313 --> 04:32.054
-Whoo! All right!
-Yeah, team!

04:32.097 --> 04:34.404
He's out of control.
He's never gonna stop.

04:34.448 --> 04:36.798
I thought he was supposed
to be a silent partner.

04:36.841 --> 04:39.409
That was non-silent.

04:39.453 --> 04:41.846
Look, your dad
is stubborn, okay?

04:41.890 --> 04:43.587
You want him
to do something,

04:43.631 --> 04:46.111
you have to make it seem
like it was his idea.

04:46.155 --> 04:49.854
So "your" plans
are "his" plans.

04:49.898 --> 04:52.988
Sounds incredibly naive
and childish.
Really?

04:53.031 --> 04:55.207
'Cause he's a grown man
who wants to put a Whack-a-Mole

04:55.251 --> 04:56.252
in your restaurant.

04:56.296 --> 04:57.427
It could work.

04:57.471 --> 05:00.343
♪♪

05:00.387 --> 05:01.823
Hey, Dad.
Got a minute?

05:01.866 --> 05:03.912
We were thinking about
your ideas for Enzo's,

05:03.955 --> 05:06.306
and they're actually
pretty great.

05:06.349 --> 05:08.351
Oh, well, I got another one
to add to the excitement.

05:08.395 --> 05:10.092
I was watching
"Urban Cowboy."

05:10.135 --> 05:12.181
Two words --
mechanical bull.

05:12.224 --> 05:15.010
Chin-don!
Right?

05:15.053 --> 05:16.011
Mechanical bull?

05:16.054 --> 05:17.795
Might be
some liability issues,

05:17.839 --> 05:19.493
what with all
of the broken necks.

05:19.536 --> 05:21.756
Nah. No, you'll be fine.
You just throw a mat down.

05:21.799 --> 05:23.671
Between that and the peanut
shells, you -- you...

05:23.714 --> 05:25.368
We'll work it out.
It'll be good.

05:25.412 --> 05:28.066
Well, let's put a pin
in the bull idea.

05:28.110 --> 05:29.198
Because we wanna get back

05:29.241 --> 05:31.026
to that other great idea
that you had.

05:31.069 --> 05:33.376
What other one?
Yeah, remember you were
talking about how you wanted

05:33.420 --> 05:35.160
to turn Enzo's
into a brew pub?

05:35.204 --> 05:38.512
Yes! You were saying something
about expanding the menu

05:38.555 --> 05:41.036
and trying new things
with the pizza crusts.

05:41.079 --> 05:43.212
I said that?
Oh, yes.

05:43.255 --> 05:45.388
Oh, it was very exciting.

05:45.432 --> 05:48.086
You were also talking about
doing wonderful new things

05:48.130 --> 05:50.350
with all of the coffees
and the dessert menu.

05:50.393 --> 05:53.396
Oh, and my absolute favorite
of your ideas

05:53.440 --> 05:55.920
was craft beers
from around the world.

05:55.964 --> 05:57.705
C-Craft beers?

05:57.748 --> 06:00.185
Oh, yes.
You're brilliant.

06:00.229 --> 06:02.057
Okay.

06:02.100 --> 06:04.233
Here's how I know
that's not true.

06:04.276 --> 06:07.628
I don't even know
what craft beers are.

06:07.671 --> 06:10.500
The only "craft" I do know
is macaroni and cheese.

06:10.544 --> 06:13.242
So I hate to break it to you,
but I never said it.

06:13.285 --> 06:17.594
Actually, sir, you said
that you thought it was --
Never said it, Chale!

06:19.161 --> 06:20.728
What's going on here?

06:20.771 --> 06:22.425
All right, Dad.

06:22.469 --> 06:25.428
The truth is, you know, we have
our own ideas for Enzo's.

06:25.472 --> 06:26.690
And we really do appreciate

06:26.734 --> 06:28.126
you helping us out
with the down payment.

06:28.170 --> 06:30.172
We really do, Mr. Gable.
Thank you.

06:30.215 --> 06:33.305
But we kinda thought you were
just gonna be an investor.

06:33.349 --> 06:35.307
You know,
like a silent partner.

06:35.351 --> 06:37.440
What, just fork over
my 80 grand

06:37.484 --> 06:39.094
and then shut my pie hole?

06:39.137 --> 06:41.401
We were hoping so, yes.

06:42.489 --> 06:44.099
Well, ya --
ya hoped wrong.

06:44.142 --> 06:46.580
Look, Dad, we know
what we're doing, okay?

06:46.623 --> 06:48.625
We did market research.
Oh, market research?

06:48.669 --> 06:50.584
Let me tell you all
the market research you need.

06:50.627 --> 06:52.673
What has ten fingers
and loves pizza?

06:52.716 --> 06:54.152
This guy!

06:54.196 --> 06:55.676
That's it!

06:55.719 --> 06:57.417
Okay, well, if someone knows
about running a business,

06:57.460 --> 06:58.940
it's thatguy,

06:58.983 --> 07:00.507
'cause that's who's been
running it for the last year.

07:00.550 --> 07:02.291
Chale has great ideas.
Oh, really?

07:02.334 --> 07:04.380
Are they the same ones
that landed him in my garage?

07:04.424 --> 07:06.121
We are staying there
to help you.

07:06.164 --> 07:07.557
Help me?!
Yeah.

07:07.601 --> 07:09.864
We cook. We clean.
We watch the kids.

07:09.907 --> 07:11.474
Yeah, and you boost
my electric bill,

07:11.518 --> 07:15.478
and he clogs my DVR with all
those British murder mysteries.

07:15.522 --> 07:16.827
[ British accent ]
"Who shot Nigel?"

07:16.871 --> 07:19.003
[ Normal voice ] I don't
know, but I wish I did,

07:19.047 --> 07:20.918
'cause he's boring
the crap out of me.

07:20.962 --> 07:22.703
It was Mrs. Pettigrew,
and I did not see it coming.

07:22.746 --> 07:24.748
Okay, babe, babe, babe,
not now.

07:24.792 --> 07:26.271
You know what?

07:26.315 --> 07:28.665
We don't have to live here.
We can find our own place.

07:28.709 --> 07:30.798
Oh, oh, actually, darling, we
have a pretty sweet deal here.

07:30.841 --> 07:32.626
No, no. You know what?
We're moving out.

07:32.669 --> 07:34.366
And we're giving you
your check back.

07:34.410 --> 07:36.804
We don't want it.
Oh, actually, darling,
we desperately want that.

07:36.847 --> 07:38.022
No.
We don't need it.

07:38.066 --> 07:39.371
We don't need anything
from you.
Fine.

07:39.415 --> 07:40.634
Then it's settled.
You know what?

07:40.677 --> 07:41.939
I'll take the money back,
and -- and --

07:41.983 --> 07:43.811
and I'll turn the garage
into a game room.

07:43.854 --> 07:45.160
Whack-a-Moles
for everybody!

07:45.203 --> 07:46.466
Sounds great.

07:46.509 --> 07:47.902
By the way,
with an extra 80 grand,

07:47.945 --> 07:49.599
I'm gonna get a dunk tank.
That's what I'll do.

07:49.643 --> 07:51.122
Oh.
Actually, those, I love.
Yeah.

07:51.166 --> 07:52.167
Actually,
you are killing me!

07:57.215 --> 07:58.739
I don't understand
what happened.

07:58.782 --> 07:59.957
My dad backed out.

08:00.001 --> 08:01.481
Enzo, is there a chance
we could just have

08:01.524 --> 08:03.308
a little more time
to get the money?

08:03.352 --> 08:05.223
I can't.
I gotta take Alviti's offer.

08:05.267 --> 08:06.224
It's now or never.

08:06.268 --> 08:07.312
I ain't getting old in here

08:07.356 --> 08:08.357
and dropping dead
on that stool

08:08.400 --> 08:10.272
the way my old man did.

08:10.315 --> 08:11.882
He died on this stool?

08:11.926 --> 08:13.101
Yeah, that exact one.

08:13.144 --> 08:15.451
Anyway, I'm sorry, kids.
I'm sorry.
No.

08:19.455 --> 08:22.240
So, wait. You guys
aren't gonna buy the place?

08:22.284 --> 08:23.590
What's gonna happen
to my beer?

08:23.633 --> 08:25.809
Look, I even had
this logo made up.

08:25.853 --> 08:28.420
It looks like your face
in a snow drift.

08:28.464 --> 08:31.554
'Cause it's my face
in a snow drift.

08:31.598 --> 08:34.296
-Hey.
-Hey.

08:34.339 --> 08:36.994
Unh-unh-unh-unh-unh. That's
where the enemy is, over there.

08:37.038 --> 08:38.561
We're not sitting
at the bar.

08:38.605 --> 08:39.910
They moved out
last night.

08:39.954 --> 08:41.521
Okay.

08:41.564 --> 08:43.087
Well, she's still
your daughter.

08:43.131 --> 08:45.133
I don't care.
I got another daughter.

08:45.176 --> 08:48.092
That's the benefit
of a two-pack.

08:48.136 --> 08:50.268
Look, I just want to find out
where Kendra and Chale

08:50.312 --> 08:53.097
are staying so I can forward
their mail. That's all.

08:53.141 --> 08:56.100
-Hi, Vanessa.
-Oh.

08:56.144 --> 08:57.754
Hi, sweetie.

08:57.798 --> 09:00.278
I'll have a --
a chicken Caesar, please.

09:00.322 --> 09:02.890
[ Coldly ] And you?

09:02.933 --> 09:05.980
I'd like to start with
a side of Drop-the-Attitude.

09:06.023 --> 09:08.591
And maybe for dessert,
you could stop being such a baby

09:08.635 --> 09:10.114
and telling me where
you and Chale are staying.

09:10.158 --> 09:11.768
How about that?
Fine.

09:11.812 --> 09:15.424
We got a room
at Hotel-It-Don't-Concern-You.

09:15.467 --> 09:16.556
I'll put your order in.

09:16.599 --> 09:19.515
She never took my order.
You see that?

09:19.559 --> 09:21.299
That's a direct shot
right there.
Okay, look.

09:21.343 --> 09:23.737
You guys just need to sit
down and talk this out.

09:23.780 --> 09:25.956
Or at least just --
How about I mediate?

09:26.000 --> 09:27.654
No, I don't want you getting
in the middle of this.

09:27.697 --> 09:28.742
Why?
Because --

09:28.785 --> 09:29.960
My family used to argue
all the time.

09:30.004 --> 09:31.614
And you know want to know
what they called me

09:31.658 --> 09:33.311
at Child Protective Services?

09:33.355 --> 09:36.184
"Lil' Peacemaker."

09:36.227 --> 09:37.794
It doesn't matter,
all right?

09:37.838 --> 09:39.143
They gotta show
a little gratitude.

09:39.187 --> 09:40.928
Oh. [ Sighs ]
They're both children, man.

09:40.971 --> 09:42.364
They need to grow up.

09:42.407 --> 09:44.888
Ooh, I'm getting spumoni!

09:44.932 --> 09:47.978
♪♪

09:48.022 --> 09:49.632
Game!

09:49.676 --> 09:50.981
Whew!

09:51.025 --> 09:52.809
All right, Dad,
you won again.

09:52.853 --> 09:54.245
Now can I go practice
my oboe?

09:54.289 --> 09:55.856
Oboe, shmoboe.
Come on.

09:55.899 --> 09:58.206
This is family fun time
right here, all right?

09:58.249 --> 09:59.555
Look, you just gotta work
on your serve.

09:59.599 --> 10:00.991
Put a little more mustard
on it, all right,

10:01.035 --> 10:02.776
and I won't be jamming it
down your throat.

10:02.819 --> 10:04.908
[ Laughs ] All right,
Sara-lish, you're up.

10:04.952 --> 10:07.563
Let's do this.
Do I have to?

10:07.607 --> 10:09.391
It doesn't feel right without
Kendra or Chale in here.

10:09.434 --> 10:11.785
What? Hey! We don't mention
their names again, okay?

10:11.828 --> 10:14.352
We are the Gables now.
The core three.

10:14.396 --> 10:15.876
In fact, you know what?
Let's take a picture.

10:15.919 --> 10:17.312
Let's do this.
Really?

10:17.355 --> 10:19.401
Yeah, yeah, and then
you're gonna text it to Kendra,

10:19.444 --> 10:21.055
and she's gonna text back,
like, "Where are you guys
having so much fun at?"

10:21.098 --> 10:22.665
And you're gonna be like,
"The place you used to live.

10:22.709 --> 10:24.188
In your face!"

10:24.232 --> 10:26.364
And then you jam on a couple
of, you know, bomb emojis

10:26.408 --> 10:28.279
and an American flag.
Let's do it.

10:28.323 --> 10:30.325
Come on, get in.
Dad, this is getting weird.

10:30.368 --> 10:31.892
You'reweird. Come on,
you're being very weird.

10:31.935 --> 10:33.676
You know, I'll do it myself.
I don't need you.

10:33.720 --> 10:35.852
There we go.
Get in here. Get in here.

10:35.896 --> 10:38.333
Close it up. All right,
everybody say "Happy Gables."

